It is a generation, 768px is one of the base model resolutions for Stable Diffusion, the other being 512px. If you want a different aspect ratio, you'll add maybe 128px or 256px to that base resolution. If you want to enlarge it, be it with img2img or ESRGAN, that's still a direct multiplication by 2 or 4. If you can divide a resolution by 128 and always get no decimals or a .5 then it came from Stable Diffusion. Then you can notice details like the strap on the arm not making sense, or the background being odd, and so on and so forth. Yes it has gotten really good with Stable Diffusion XL and with Stable Cascade and SD3 it's gonna get even better, but the resolution giveaway will always be there.
